2000_January 25 

A lot has been said about this historical breakthrough in the art of
cinematography. Of course, outstanding FX and soundtrack do a good job as
key-components of a normal blockbuster. Good play of actors also adds some
extra points. However, there is something that distinguishes the Matrix from
all other successful science fiction movies. And this is not the extensively
debated technological superiority but the specific spirit and philosophy,
that is, the IDEA behind the screenplay. How can we explain injustice and
cruelty of the world around us? Why is it so imperfect? 
